Standard and Poor's Corp said itaffirmed Security Pacific Corp's 4.5 billion dlrs of debt.    S and P said that although the bank's decision today toincrease its reserve against developing country debt by 500 mlndlrs will result in a loss in the second quarter, the firmstill expects to report a profit for the year.    Affirmed were Security Pacific's AA senior debt, AA-minussubordinated debt and preferred stock and A-1-plus commercialpaper. Also, uninsured certificates of deposit of SecurityPacific National Bank and Arizona Bank of Phoenix were affirmedat AA/A-1-plus. Reuter&#3;